"content": "This is a superb must-read piece by @Ayaan that explains the transformation of our universities from institutions that seek to educate the next generation of leaders to advance society, to ideological indoctrination institutes that graduate the likes of @ZohranKMamdani.  \n\nIf you wonder why American taxpayers question why their funds should go to these universities, read this piece and it will be abundantly clear. \n\nThe problems at universities are principally in the ‘studies’ degrees, but federal funding is being withdrawn from the STEM departments. (This is because the studies’ degree programs don’t qualify for much federal funding).\n\nOur government is withdrawing funding  from @Harvard, @Columbia and other problematic universities because money is fungible, and sending taxpayer money to institutions educating the future enemies of our country is contrary to the interests of our nation. \n\nA potential solution to this problem is for universities to spinoff their science and other STEM departments that receive federal funding into new independent entities that are independently financed and governed. This approach will also have the beneficial effect of helping them increase donations from alumni and others who want their funds directed to programs that advance society’s interests rather than siphoned off to other areas that the donors did not intend to support. The risk of Federal funding and charitable donation ‘overhead allocations’ being misused and/or misdirected will be largely eliminated.  \n\nBy separating STEM into separate universities, the studies degree programs will also have to be sustained with independent funding, which will increase scrutiny of these departments and their activities.  Closer scrutiny by alumni and other outside observers of these program areas will help balance the anti-American radicalism that has emerged in these departments.",
